params.newKernel_: Address of the new kernel contract.

params.amount: Amount of the token transferred to the escrow

params.order: Rental order for which to settle a payment.

params.orders: Rental ordesr for which to settle payments.

params.to: Address to send the collected tokens.
params.token: Address of the token to skim.

params.newImplementation: Address of the implementation contract to upgrade to.

INIT().notice: Initialization function for the module which is called when the module is         first installed or upgraded by the kernel. Can only be called by the kernel.

KEYCODE().notice: Defines the keycode for this module.

MODULE_PROXY_INSTANTIATION(address).notice: Instantiates this contract as a module via a proxy.

VERSION().notice: Specifies which version of a module is being implemented.

changeKernel(address).notice: Points the adapter to reference a new kernel address. This function can         only be called by the active kernel, and is used to perform migrations by         telling all policies and modules where the new kernel is located before         actually performing the migration.

freeze().notice: Freezes the contract which prevents upgrading the implementation contract.         There is no way to unfreeze once a contract has been frozen.

increaseDeposit(address,uint256).notice: When fungible tokens are transferred to the payment escrow contract,         their balances should be increased.

proxiableUUID().notice: Returns the ID of this `Proxiable` contract.

setFee(uint256).notice: Sets the numerator for the fee. The denominator will always be set at         10,000.

settlePayment((bytes32,(uint8,uint8,addr.notice: Settles the payment for a rental order by transferring all items marked as         payments to their destination accounts. During the settlement process, if         active, a fee is taken on the payment.

settlePaymentBatch((bytes32,(uint8,uint8.notice: Settles the payments for multiple orders by looping through each one.

skim(address,address).notice: Used to collect protocol fees. In addition, if funds are accidentally sent         to the payment escrow contract, this function can be used to skim them off.

upgrade(address).notice: Upgrades the contract to a different implementation. This implementation         contract must be compatible with ERC-1822 or else the upgrade will fail.
